name: Sushi
description: Vinegared rice with various toppings such as raw fish or vegetables.

name: Tacos
description: Soft or crispy tortillas filled with ingredients like meat, beans, and cheese.

name: Pasta Carbonara
description: Pasta with a creamy sauce made from eggs, cheese, pancetta, and pepper.

name: Borscht
description: A beet soup that is often served hot or cold, sometimes with sour cream.

name: Baklava
description: A sweet pastry made of layers of filo dough filled with nuts and honey or syrup.

name: Dim Sum
description: A variety of small, flavorful dishes like dumplings, buns, and rolls, often enjoyed with tea.

name: Croissant
description: A buttery, flaky pastry that’s often enjoyed for breakfast.

name: Ceviche
description: Fresh seafood marinated in citrus juices with onions, cilantro, and chili peppers.

name: Poutine
description: French fries topped with cheese curds and smothered in gravy.

name: Bunny Chow
description: A hollowed-out loaf of bread filled with curry.

name: Balut
description: A fertilized duck egg with a partially developed embryo, commonly eaten as a street food in the Philippines.

name: Surströmming
description: Fermented herring from Sweden, known for its strong odor and pungent flavor.

name: Hákarl
description: Icelandic fermented shark meat with a distinctive ammonia-rich smell and strong taste.

name: Casu Marzu
description: A Sardinian cheese infested with live insect larvae, considered a delicacy in Italy.

name: Kopi Luwak
description: Coffee made from beans eaten and excreted by civet cats, known for its unique flavor and high cost.

name: Century Egg
description: Preserved egg, typically duck or chicken, that has been aged and pickled in a mixture of clay, ash, and quicklime.

name: Rocky Mountain Oysters
description: Deep-fried bull testicles, often served as a novelty dish in parts of the United States.

name: Fugu
description: Pufferfish delicacy from Japan that contains poisonous toxins; only specially licensed chefs can prepare it safely.

name: Natto
description: Fermented soybeans with a strong flavor, sticky texture, and a distinct smell, popular in Japan.

name: Blood Sausage
description: Sausage made from blood, typically pig or cow, mixed with grains and spices.
